- id: M1002
  name: "Blameshifting"
  description: >
    The act of shifting responsibility for one's own mistakes, negative feelings, or problems onto another person to deflect blame and avoid accountability. This is a common defense mechanism in conflicts, where the individual frames the other person's actions or characteristics as the direct cause of their own negative behavior or outcomes.
